The paper proposes a multi-task learning framework for Machine Reading Comprehension (MRC) and discusses the use of out-domain data to learn robust and general contextual representations. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Natural Language Processing (NLP) sub-category of Computer Science (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of pre-trained representation models, which are commonly used in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also evaluates its approach on various datasets, which suggests that it may belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a novel approach to multi-task learning, which may also be relevant to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
